


3/10/2021 - Arrays 5

-sort() method
-Arrays.sort(array); //ordered
-it is used to sort an array
-if array is int array, then it will be sorted from smallest to biggest
-if array is String array, then it will be sorted alphabetically

-binarySearch(array, key)
-it used to search an element in an array
-it will return an int which the index of key found
-the result will be negative if key is not found
-if the result zero or positive, then it means the key is found and the index returned is the position-location of that key

-MULTI-DIMENSIONAL ARRAY
-Array inside the array
-It is preferred to create tables-matrixes
-Syntax:

2-dimensional array
int[][] numbers = {{1,2,3}, {1,2}};

numbers[0][2] = 3;

System.out.println(Arrays.toDeepString(numbers)); // [[1,2,3], [1,2]]

for(int i = 0; i < numbers.length; i++){
	for(int j = 0; j < numbers[i].length; j++){
	 System.out.println(numbers[i][j]);
	}
}
